T he declensions of adjectives and participles are the same as the first three declensions of nouns. The masculine and neuter genders always follow the second or third declension. The feminine generally follows the first. In all cases, however, any one gender always holds to a single declension. Con- sequently within any one gender the coincidences in form are never more numerous than those of a similarly declined noun of one of the first three declensions.
